    "content_hash": "7ac071afed99e628",
    "department": "Client Service",
    "description": "Riveron is looking for a OneStream Administrator to join our Technology and Innovation practice. The OneStream Administrator supports the day-to-day administration, maintenance, and optimization of the OneStream CPM platform. This role partners closely with Accounting, Finance, and IT to support GAAP-based financial reporting, ensure system stability, data accuracy, and timely resolution of application issues. The ideal candidate has hands-on OneStream experience, a working knowledge of GAAP reporting, and is looking to deepen technical and functional expertise within a financial systems environment.\n\n\n\n\nWho You Are:\n\n - 2+ years of hands-on OneStream experience in an administrator, analyst, or support role\n\n - Bachelor's degree in Accounting, Finance, Information Systems, Computer Science, or a related field\n\n - Working knowledge of GAAP financial reporting and consolidation concepts\n\n - Experience supporting financial systems through a ticketing or application support model\n\n - Familiarity with data integrations, transformation rules, and reconciliation process\n\n - Experience supporting GAAP consolidations, eliminations, and intercompany accounting in OneStream\n\n - OneStream Administrator or related certification\n\n - Exposure to OneStream calculations, business rules, and reporting components\n\nWhat You'll Do:\n\n - Serve as a primary point of contact for OneStream-related support requests through the organization's ticketing system\n\n - Triage, analyze, and resolve user issues related to data loads, reports, dashboards, workflows, and security\n\n - Support GAAP reporting by resolving issues impacting financial statements and management reporting\n\n - Escalate complex issues to senior administrators or external consultants as needed\n\n - Track issues through resolution and communicate status clearly to stakeholders\n\n - Administer and support OneStream applications, including dimensions, hierarchies, metadata, and security\n\n - Assist with user access, roles, and profiles to support GAAP reporting requirements\n\n - Support chart of accounts, legal entity structures, and reporting rollups used for external and management reporting\n\n - Monitor application performance and assist with optimization efforts\n\n - Support and troubleshoot data loads from ERPs and other source systems into OneStream\n\n - Analyze and resolve data load, mapping, and transformation issues\n\n - Participate in testing of enhancements, new builds, and patches in non-production environments\n\nAbout Riveron:\n\nAt Riveron, we partner with clients—from global multinationals to high-growth private entities—to solve complex finance challenges, guided by our DELTA values: Drive, Excellence, Leadership, Teamwork, and Accountability. Our entrepreneurial culture thrives on collaboration, diverse perspectives, and delivering exceptional outcomes. We are committed to fostering growth, both for our clients and our people, through mentorship, integrity, and a client-centric approach. This inclusive environment offers flexibility, progressive benefits, and meaningful opportunities for impactful work that supports well-being in and out of the office.\n\nCheck us out on social media:\n\nLinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/company/riveron/life/culture/ Glassdoor https://www.glassdoor.com/Photos/Riveron-Office-Photos-E672242.htm Instagram https://www.instagram.com/riveronconsulting/ Facebook https://www.facebook.com/RiveronConsulting/\n\nRiveron Consulting is an Equal Opportunity Employer and believes that we are stronger together through our diversity. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, age, national origin, disability status, protected veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or any other characteristic protected by law.\n\nFull time roles are eligible for a full range of benefits including medical, dental, and vision insurance, 401(k) with company match, and PTO. A complete description of all available benefits can be found at Riveron's Benefits page at https://riveron.com/riveron-life/. Contract roles are not eligible for benefits.\n\n\nFRAUD ALERT\n\nPlease beware of fraudulent schemes or impersonations when going through the job application process. A Riveron employee will never recruit via text or extend unsolicited employment offers. Additionally, a Riveron employee will never ask you to exchange money or purchase anything as part of the recruiting process.\n\n\nWE MAY USE ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE (AI) TOOLS TO SUPPORT PARTS OF THE HIRING PROCESS, SUCH AS REVIEWING APPLICATIONS, ANALYZING RESUMES, OR ASSESSING RESPONSES. THESE TOOLS ASSIST OUR RECRUITMENT TEAM BUT DO NOT REPLACE HUMAN JUDGMENT. FINAL HIRING DECISIONS ARE ULTIMATELY MADE BY HUMANS. IF YOU WOULD LIKE MORE INFORMATION ABOUT HOW YOUR DATA IS PROCESSED, PLEASE CONTACT US.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
